cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CG 

The paper deals with spatial queries in the context of virtual reality, which involves computer graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of Redirected Walking (RW) and the formulation of the Dual-world Redirected-walking Obstacle-free Path (DROP) involve algorithmic techniques and optimization, which are relevant to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses index structures and range queries, which are related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
